    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Just use this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;SomeBean&gt; newList = new ArrayList&lt;SomeBean&gt;(otherList);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Note: still not thread safe, if you modify <code>otherList</code> from another thread, then you may want to make that <code>otherList</code> (and even <code>newList</code>) a <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/concurrent/CopyOnWriteArrayList.html\"><code>CopyOnWriteArrayList</code></a>, for instance -- or use a lock primitive, such as <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/concurrent/locks/ReentrantReadWriteLock.html\">ReentrantReadWriteLock</a> to serialize read/write access to whatever lists are concurrently accessed.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 23121,
      "reputation" : 535127,
      "user_id" : 57695,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 75,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/53ee9941b3fefef67175daf212e62d41?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Peter Lawrey",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/57695/peter-lawrey"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 8,
    "last_activity_date" : 1358171916,
    "last_edit_date" : 1592644375,
    "creation_date" : 1358171916,
    "answer_id" : 14319831,
    "question_id" : 14319732,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<blockquote>\n<p>I tried to do something like this, but I still got an IndexOutOfBoundsException.</p>\n<p>I got a ConcurrentAccessException</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This means you are modifying the list while you are trying to copy it, most likely in another thread.  To fix this you have to either</p>\n<ul>\n<li><p>use a collection which is designed for concurrent access.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>lock the collection appropriately so you can iterate over it (or allow you to call a method which does this for you)</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>find a away to avoid needing to copy the original list.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 18059693,
        "reputation" : 669,
        "user_id" : 13127098,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/afPf2.jpg?s=256",
        "display_name" : "Nakul Goyal",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/13127098/nakul-goyal"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 0,
