    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>re: <code>indexOutOfBoundsException</code>, your sublist args are the problem; you need to end the sublist at size-1.  Being zero-based, the last element of a list is always size-1, there is no element in the size position, hence the error.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6415895,
      "reputation" : 27,
      "user_id" : 4974103,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/9d0f11b4a97809e3d825f7206aa184aa?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "weixingsun",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4974103/weixingsun"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : -3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1433427636,
    "creation_date" : 1433427636,
    "answer_id" : 30646408,
    "question_id" : 14319732,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>subList function is a trick, the returned object is still in the original list.\nso if you do any operation in subList, it will cause the concurrent exception in your code, no matter it is single thread or multi thread.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4423722,
      "reputation" : 14310,
      "user_id" : 4374291,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 80,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/0bj79.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "T04435",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4374291/t04435"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1444969491,
    "creation_date" : 1444969491,
    "answer_id" : 33162547,
    "question_id" : 14319732,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I was having the same problem <strong>ConcurrentAccessException</strong> and mysolution was to:</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;SomeBean&gt; tempList = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();\n\nfor (CartItem item : prodList) {\n  tempList.add(item);\n}\nprodList.clear();\nprodList = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;(tempList);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>So it works only one operation at the time and avoids the Exeption...</p>\n"
  }, {
