    "question_id" : 14319732,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I can't see any correct answer. If you want a deep copy you have to iterate and copy object manually (you could use a copy constructor).</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 18317196,
      "reputation" : 1,
      "user_id" : 13338739,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjGYIur7u3UaKvcWCSMKlZhTD0tWg4-mfgVEbHUjA=k-s256",
      "display_name" : "XGsm Prj",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/13338739/xgsm-prj"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1607173057,
    "last_edit_date" : 1607173057,
    "creation_date" : 1607111142,
    "answer_id" : 65149783,
    "question_id" : 14319732,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You should use the <code>addAll</code> method. It appends all of the elements in the specified collection to the end of the copy list. It will be a copy of your list.</p>\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; myList = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();\nmyList.add(&quot;a&quot;);\nmyList.add(&quot;b&quot;);\nList&lt;String&gt; copyList = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();\ncopyList.addAll(myList);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 11722489,
      "reputation" : 162,
      "user_id" : 8581009,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/RuLTr.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Dan",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/8581009/dan"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1641599473,
    "creation_date" : 1641599473,
    "answer_id" : 70628419,
    "question_id" : 14319732,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>just in case you use Lombok:</p>\n<p>mark SomeBean with the following annotation:</p>\n<pre><code>@Builder(toBuilder = true, builderMethodName = &quot;&quot;)\n</code></pre>\n<p>and Lombok will perform a shallow copy of objects for you using copy constructor:</p>\n<pre><code>inputList.stream()\n         .map(x -&gt; x.toBuilder().build())\n         .collect(Collectors.toList());\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 25974568,
      "reputation" : 122,
      "user_id" : 19689190,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AFdZucrKnFlWWf0ntw_HMSIIpSFqFPefuSK_Dk9PIFG2=k-s256",
      "display_name" : "Amar kumar Nayak",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/19689190/amar-kumar-nayak"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1715621879,
    "last_edit_date" : 1715621879,
    "creation_date" : 1715618374,
    "answer_id" : 78473676,
    "question_id" : 14319732,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Java 10 provide one feature like How to copy one collection to another collection</p>\n<p><code>copyOf()</code> is used to simple copy a collection(List,Set,Map);</p>\n<h1>Syntax</h1>\n<pre><code>List&lt;E&gt; list=new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();\n\nList&lt;E&gt; li2=List.copyOf(list);\n</code></pre>\n<h1>Rule</h1>\n<ol>\n<li>This method return immutable collection.</li>\n<li>If you want to modifie you got java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException.</li>\n<li>Null value not allowed</li>\n</ol>\n<pre><code>List&lt;SomeBean&gt; wsList = app.allInOne(template);\n\nList&lt;SomeBean&gt; wsListCopy=List.copyOf(wsList);\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
